{{Other uses|Deck (disambiguation){{!}}Deck}}
<!--TEMPORARY USE OF Infobox bridge type UNTIL A SPECIFIC "type" INFOBOX IS AVAILABLE:--> {{Main article|Deck (building)}} [[File:上海国际金融中心.jpg|thumb|View of [[Shanghai World Financial Center]] as viewed from the [[Shanghai Tower]], at the 118th floor observatory 548m above ground]] [[File:Niagara Falls - ON - Skylon Tower (Aussichtsdeck).jpg|thumb|Visitors on the observation deck of the Skylon Tower overlooking Niagara Falls]] [[File:Two World Trade Center Observation Deck.jpg|thumb|right|Midtown Manhattan in the distance. Photo taken at Two World Trade Center's observation deck, in the 1980s]] [[File:Glass balconies St Eusebius Church Arnhem NL.jpg|thumb|Glass balconies St Eusebius Church, Arnhem, The Netherlands.jpg]]
An '''observation deck''', '''observation platform''' or '''viewing platform''' is an elevated [[Tourism|sightseeing]] platform usually situated upon a tall architectural structure such as a [[skyscraper]] or [[observation tower]]. Observation decks are sometimes enclosed from weather, and a few may include coin-operated telescopes for viewing distant features.
